					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This inscription records a gift of gold for a perpetual lamp to the temple of Śrī Pōndaip-perumānaḍigaḷ, at Rājamallach-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Tiruvēgambapuram by certain Gaṇyaṉ Iraṇasarmaṉ, a native of Māṅgāḍu. The temple committee named <hi rend="italic">gaṇapperumakkaḷ</hi> was left in charge of burning the lamp with the interest accrued from the donated gold.</p>						

						</summary>
